# React + Vite — Components & Hooks (Part 3)

## 15. Custom Hooks

Business logic belongs in hooks.

Example `shared/hooks/useDebounce.ts`:

```ts
import { useState, useEffect } from 'react'

export function useDebounce<T>(value: T, delay = 300) {
  const [debounced, setDebounced] = useState(value)
  useEffect(() => {
    const timer = setTimeout(() => setDebounced(value), delay)
    return () => clearTimeout(timer)
  }, [value, delay])
  return debounced
}
```

Rules:
- `use` prefix mandatory
- Keep hooks pure and testable

## 16. Component Guidelines

- Functional components only (React.FC seldom needed).
- Single responsibility principle.
- Keep files < 200 LOC.
- Extract side-effects to hooks.
- Use presentational / container separation when complexity grows.
- Use tailwind/css-modules or design system tokens.
- Prefer semantic elements (`<header>`, `<main>`, `<nav>`, `<article>`, `<button>`, `<label>`) over generic `div`/`span` where meaning exists (see Part 4 — Accessibility).
- Use `key` with stable, unique IDs for lists; avoid index when items are reordered, added, or removed.

Example:

```tsx
type Props = { title: string }

export function Card({ title }: Props) {
  return <article className="card"><h2>{title}</h2></article>
}
```

## 16b. Reusable Components

Place in `shared/components/`. Design for composition and configurability.

Rules:
- Accept `children` or render props when layout varies.
- Use clear, typed props; optional props with sensible defaults.
- Variants via props (e.g. `variant: 'primary' | 'secondary'`) not separate components.
- Document props in JSDoc or separate types file.
- Export from `shared/components/index.ts` for clean imports.

Example reusable `Button`:

```tsx
type ButtonProps = React.ButtonHTMLAttributes<HTMLButtonElement> & {
  variant?: 'primary' | 'secondary' | 'ghost'
  size?: 'sm' | 'md' | 'lg'
  isLoading?: boolean
}

export function Button({ variant = 'primary', size = 'md', isLoading, children, disabled, ...rest }: ButtonProps) {
  return (
    <button
      className={clsx('btn', `btn-${variant}`, `btn-${size}`)}
      disabled={disabled || isLoading}
      {...rest}
    >
      {isLoading ? <Spinner /> : children}
    </button>
  )
}
```

For complex reusable components (Modal, DataTable, FormField), colocate in `shared/components/` with sub-components or compound components when needed.

## 16c. forwardRef

Use `forwardRef` when the component must expose a DOM ref (e.g. inputs, custom buttons used with refs). Forward to the underlying native element.

```tsx
import { forwardRef } from 'react'

export const Input = forwardRef<HTMLInputElement, InputProps>(
  (props, ref) => <input ref={ref} {...props} />
)
```

Use `useImperativeHandle` only when you need to expose a custom API (e.g. `focus()`, `scrollIntoView()`).

## 16d. Error Boundary

Shared `ErrorBoundary` with retry and fallback. Use for route or feature-level isolation.

```tsx
import { ErrorBoundary } from 'react-error-boundary'

export function ErrorFallback({ error, resetErrorBoundary }) {
  return (
    <div role="alert">
      <p>{error?.message}</p>
      <Button onClick={resetErrorBoundary}>Retry</Button>
    </div>
  )
}
```

## 16e. Loading & Skeleton

Provide `PageLoader` (full-page) and `Skeleton` for content placeholders. Match skeleton layout to real content to avoid layout shift (CLS). Use for Suspense fallbacks and `isLoading` states.

## 16f. Toast / Notification

Use a provider (e.g. `react-hot-toast`, `sonner`, `notistack`). Wrap app with provider. Call `toast.success()`, `toast.error()` from sagas, mutations, or interceptors. Keep messages short and actionable.

## 16g. Layout Primitives

Shared `PageLayout`, `Sidebar`, `Header`, `Footer` in `shared/components/layout/`. PageLayout typically: header + main + optional sidebar. Use composition via `children` and slots (e.g. `header`, `sidebar`, `content`).

## 16h. Empty State

Dedicated component for "no data" / "no results". Accept `title`, `description`, optional `action` (CTA). Use when list/table is empty or search returns nothing.

## 16i. Context Usage

Use Context for: theme, locale, modal state, narrowly scoped UI state. Avoid for server data or global app state (prefer Redux/React Query). Keep context value stable (memoize) to avoid unnecessary re-renders. Prefer composition over deep context when possible.

## 16j. Compound Components

For Modal, Tabs, Accordion: expose sub-components (`Modal.Header`, `Modal.Body`, `Modal.Footer`) that share implicit context. Use `React.createContext` or `React.Children` + `cloneElement`. Keeps API flexible and composable.

```tsx
<Modal>
  <Modal.Header title="Edit" />
  <Modal.Body>...</Modal.Body>
  <Modal.Footer><Button>Save</Button></Modal.Footer>
</Modal>
```

## 17. CSS & Styling

### 17a. Tailwind Setup

`tailwind.config.js` — set content paths to scan for classes:

```js
export default {
  content: ['./index.html', './src/**/*.{js,ts,jsx,tsx}'],
  theme: { extend: {} },
  plugins: []
}
```

Entry: `src/index.css` with `@tailwind base; @tailwind components; @tailwind utilities;`. Import in `main.tsx`.

### 17b. Design Tokens

Define spacing, typography, colors, radii, shadows in `tailwind.config.js` or CSS variables. Keep tokens in one place; reference in components.

```js
// tailwind.config.js
theme: {
  extend: {
    colors: { primary: { 50: '...', 500: '...', 900: '...' } },
    spacing: { 18: '4.5rem' },
    borderRadius: { '4xl': '2rem' }
  }
}
```

Or CSS variables: `--color-primary`, `--spacing-md`, `--radius-lg`.

### 17c. Global vs Scoped

- **Global**: `src/index.css` or `src/app/global.css` — resets, base typography, CSS variables.
- **Scoped**: Tailwind utility classes (preferred) or CSS Modules (`.module.css`) for component-specific styles. Avoid inline styles except for dynamic values.

### 17d. Z-Index Scale

Use a named scale to avoid conflicts. Example in Tailwind or CSS:

```css
:root {
  --z-dropdown: 100;
  --z-sticky: 200;
  --z-modal: 300;
  --z-toast: 400;
}
```

### 17e. Breakpoints

Tailwind defaults: `sm` 640px, `md` 768px, `lg` 1024px, `xl` 1280px. Extend in config if needed. Mobile-first: base styles for mobile, add `md:` and up for larger screens.

### 17f. Animation & Transitions

Define duration and easing tokens. Use Tailwind `transition-*`, `animate-*` or CSS custom properties. Prefer `prefers-reduced-motion: reduce` for accessibility.

### 17g. Tailwind Conventions

- Prefer utility classes over `@apply` in component CSS (better tree-shaking).
- Use `cn()` (clsx + twMerge) to merge and override classes.
- Extract repeated utility combos into components, not `@apply` blocks.
- Avoid arbitrary values (`w-[137px]`) when a token exists.

### 17h. CSS Modules (Alternative)

File: `Component.module.css`. Import: `import styles from './Component.module.css'`. Use `className={styles.card}`. Names are auto-scoped.
